title: IXPE X-ray observatory completes commissioning, eyes Cassiopeia A for calibration
summary: The pioneering Imaging X-ray Polarimeter Explorer (IXPE) telescope, the first observatory in space to perform detailed polarimetry of some of the highest-energy objects the universe has to offer, has ended its highly-successful commissioning phase just over 30 days after lifting off from the Kennedy Space Center on December 9, 2021, on a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket.

title: SpaceX goes all-in on Starship configuration for second-gen Starlink
summary: SpaceX has dropped a plan to use Falcon 9 to launch the 30,000 satellites in its proposed second-generation Starlink broadband constellation, and is instead focusing on a configuration leveraging its upcoming Starship vehicle.

title: Biden nominates Navy admiral to run National Geospatial Intelligence Agency
summary: President Biden has nominated U.S. Navy Vice Adm. Frank Whitworth to be the next director of the National Geospatial Intelligence Agency, the. Defense Department announced Jan. 10.

title: NASA Invites Media to Meet New Chief Scientist, Climate Advisor
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 11 a.m. EST Tuesday, Jan. 11, to introduce and discuss the role of the agency’s new chief scientist and senior climate advisor.

title: Defense Innovation Unit taps Lyten to develop high-performance batteries for small satellites
summary: Lyten, a battery manufacturer based in California, has prototyped an advanced battery design for small satellites under a contract from the Defense Innovation Unit.

title: NASA Announces New Chief Scientist, Senior Climate Advisor
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson announced that Dr. Katherine Calvin will serve the agency in dual roles as chief scientist and senior climate advisor effective Monday.

title: SOFIA makes case for continued operations
summary: Officials with a NASA airborne observatory responded to a stinging rebuke in the latest astrophysics decadal survey by arguing that the facility, targeted for termination, is essential to the agency’s broader science program.
